1978;;Remember My Name;;American;;Alan Rudolph;;Geraldine Chaplin, Anthony Perkins, Moses Gunn;;thriller;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Remember_My_Name;;Neil Curry (Perkins) is living a happy life with his second wife Barbara (Berenson) in California after abandoning his first wife, Emily (Chaplin), in New York. Their life of domestic bliss is interrupted when Emily comes back from prison, where she served a 12-year sentence for murdering Neil's former lover. She arrives in California to wreak havoc and also to claim back Neil.[2]